## Objective
Create a WorkflowCard component for the Helm dashboard.

## Working Directory
`Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/`

## Create: `dashboard/WorkflowCard.tsx`

A card that shows a workflow's live status, step chain, outcomes, and actions.

Props:
```typescript
interface WorkflowCardProps {
  workflow: {
    id: string;
    name: string;
    description?: string;
    definition: any;
    compiled_spec?: any;
    invocation_count: number;
    last_invoked_at?: string;
  };
  trigger?: {
    id: string;
    event_type: string;
    enabled: boolean;
    cron_expression?: string;
    last_fired_at?: string;
    fire_count: number;
  } | null;
  latestRun?: {
    run_id: string;
    status: string;
    total_jobs: number;
    completed_jobs: number;
    created_at?: string;
    finished_at?: string;
  } | null;
  onEdit: () => void;
  onViewResults: () => void;
  onTrigger: () => void;
  onRunNow: () => void;
}
```

Layout:
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Workflow Name                              STATUS BADGE │
│  Step1 → Step2 → Step3 → Step4    (small colored pills) │
│                                                          │
│  47 runs · Last: 4m ago · Next: 11 PM                   │
│  [View Results]  [Edit]  [Run Now]  [Trigger ▼]         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Status badge:
- LIVE (green pulsing dot + text) — has enabled trigger
- SCHEDULED (blue) — has cron trigger
- PAUSED (gray) — has disabled trigger
- DRAFT (dashed border) — no trigger, never run

Step chain: extract step labels from `compiled_spec.jobs[]` and render as small pills connected by → arrows. Use amber (#F5A623) for agent steps, green for check, blue for API, purple for human.

Outcome line: show `invocation_count` runs, time since `last_invoked_at`, and next scheduled time if cron trigger exists.

Action buttons use `.builder-btn` CSS class for consistency.

